    id: 39,
    slug: "anthropic-project-glasswing-claude-mythos-withheld",
    title: "Anthropic Is Holding Back Its Most Capable Model. That's a First.",
    summary: "Claude Mythos won't ship publicly. Access is limited to select partners under Project Glasswing, citing cybersecurity risk. The frontier just developed an unshipped tier.",
    body: [
      "Anthropic confirmed on April 7 what a March 26 internal leak had already made plain: its most capable model, internally called Claude Mythos, will not be publicly released. Access is restricted to a small number of partners under a program the company is calling Project Glasswing, with cybersecurity risk cited as the reason.",
      "This is new territory. Every frontier lab up to now — OpenAI, Google DeepMind, xAI, Meta, Anthropic itself — has shipped its most capable model to end users, with guardrails layered on top. The implicit deal was: capability is the product, and we'll moderate the dangerous edges at inference time. Project Glasswing breaks that pattern.",
      "The cybersecurity specifics Anthropic pointed to are not hand-wavy. Mythos reportedly demonstrated strong performance on autonomous exploitation chains — finding vulnerabilities, writing working exploits against them, and chaining them through multi-step intrusions without human guidance at the individual steps. That's the capability class that has kept national-security researchers nervous for two years. It's apparently here.",
      "The industry reaction will be interesting to watch. If Anthropic's competitors have models at or near this capability tier, they now face a harder decision about whether to ship theirs. If they ship and something bad happens downstream — mass-scale automated intrusion, for example — Anthropic's restraint becomes evidence at whatever hearing follows. If they don't ship, the commercial pressure of holding back a working model while Anthropic's partners extract value from theirs is significant.",
      "One thing worth flagging: the only public information we have about Mythos's actual capabilities comes from Anthropic itself and the March leak. There's no independent red-team writeup, no external benchmark report. Trust-but-verify applies as much to a company restraining a model as one releasing it.",
      "For teams building on the Claude API, this doesn't change anything today — the publicly available Claude Sonnet 4.6 and Opus 4.7 lines continue to ship and evolve. But the existence of a deliberately unshipped tier above them is the story everyone in the space is going to be chewing on for months.",
    ],
